      <talk_answer link_index="n1619_sidel-1-a" mid="31" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="7"><![CDATA[<html>$Cidel$<BR>The reason why Kayleen agreed to send court sorceresses to guard the Monolith is because this is a serious matter that concerns the safety of this world. But the people who still hate me are viewing Kayleen as a traitor thinking that she's doing it for me.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1619_sidel-1-a" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1619_sidel-1-b" mid="32" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="8"><![CDATA[<html>$Cidel$<BR>And Kayleen treats Terramai with respect even though sorceresses are not on good terms with clerics. She does that because he was Karacule's friend, but the other sorceresses are saying that she must have an ulterior motive... They even say I came to Anu Arendel to help so as to get something from the Royal Castle.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1619_sidel-1-b" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1619_sidel-1-c" mid="33" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>That sounds complicated. </html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="9"><![CDATA[<html>$Cidel$<BR>The sorceresses who support me are suspicious of Kayleen to. Tamara is one of them.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1619_sidel-1-c" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1619_sidel-1-d" mid="34" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>Maybe they just don't understand...</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="10"><![CDATA[<html>$Cidel$<BR>As the leader of Fairystar, I'm embarrassed that such internal arguments are distracting everyone when we should be worrying about the nearing end of this world. </html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1619_sidel-1-d" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1619_sidel-1-e" mid="35" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>Cidel, you're so smart.</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="11"><![CDATA[<html>$Cidel$<BR>So I'm thinking maybe we should let everyone know how dangerous the situation is right now. That will give them a common cause to fight for.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1619_sidel-1-e" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1619_sidel-2" mid="36" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>Sure.</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="12"><![CDATA[<html>$Cidel$<BR>Not at all... I always think you're the wiser one who knows when to act. <BR>So can you go to the <FONT color=#387206>area near the Monolith</FONT> and get rid of the <FONT color=#7e12d2>monsters</FONT> and collect some data for me?<BR>Thanks.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
